parameters: MC
There was a lot of dirt and rock that was
filling the tower into the temple. Honestly,
this probably took the most amount of time
now that I'm thinking about it... Worth it!
A
MC
Even more of the dirt I pulled out of the
tower. If I remember right, it took me about a
year just to dig enough dirt out to enter the
temple or church underground.
B
MC
I remember having to take a week off due to
straining my back after one particularly heavy
haul of this dirt. After that, I took my time
since I couldn't work on making my way to
MC
the inside of the temple to study the history
if I couldn't dig.
C
MC
I honestly started wishing I spent half my
money for this dig for an earth orb at about
the half way point. If I had, the job would
have been done so much faster.
MC
That being said though, I probably wouldn't
have had enough money to do the rest of this
dig. It was a hard choice, but staying here
longer was the better choice.
MC
After all, the longer I stay, the more I
discover and learn about the people who lived
and worked here. I would LOVE to unbury the
entire temple, but that would take too long.
D
MC
Is there really anything else left to say about
piles of dirt? It's just dirt.
Documentation of everything she's found here as well
as order fourms and maps of this contenent. She even does some
of her duties as a princess from here, although she'll just
call it annoying work that gets in the way of history.
MC
All of the books that helped me learn how to do
digs like these without harming any of the
relics inside. I made sure to read them letter
by letter before I moved anything I found.
MC
Good lord do I hate this scarecrow I made, but
it works, and that's what matters. I need these
crops to stay alive, so I just have to deal
with it.
MC
Can't study history if I'm starving to death
after all. Even I know that much. What I
wouldn't give to not need food and water
to survive so I can continue studying.
MC
Looks like the crops are almost reaady to
harvest, so that will be nice when they're
ready to collect.
If MC brings in excess dirt into the temple, she'd never
forgive herself for ruining the sanctanty of the place,
so she takes a bath at least once a day, sometimes 2 depending
on her activities on that given day.
MC
I have to take a bath every day to avoid
bringing outside dirt into the temple. If I
were to do that, I'd ruin the integrety of
the temple inside.
I'll take a bath now since I've just woken up.
MC
There we go, perfectly clean! Time for history!
A
I'm more than okay with taking another bath. The cleaner the
better for preserving history!
MC
There we go, perfectly clean! Time for history!
MC
My charcoal making pit. I may still have some
ink, but it's not enough for everything I need
to document, so I've had to make my own
charcoal over my time here.
MC
Luckily it's something I can set then forget
until it's done. Just need to make sure I check
for fire spreading every so often.
MC
Berries that ______ brought me on their last
visit. I'm just glad that they know how to
protect themselves. I rely on her too much for
stuff that I can't get myself.
MC
A special ink I have to use for my job.
Wish I didn't have to do this job, but it's
kept a little bit of money coming in.
MC
Why did he send me these plates? I mean, I
know why, he wants my approval on their design
but doesn't he have someone hired for that? An
artist that he passes all designs by?
MC
Ah whatever. They look nice enough, but I'm
going to assume that's not enough for him...
I'll figure out how to respond later.
MC
A design on it that looks like a spider,
and one that looks like a skull... if this
doesn't scream "This plate hails from the
Kingdom of Death!" I don't know what does.
MC
So... many... PLATES! I don't need this many
to approve of a design for them!
MC
Ahh, the life of someone who can read most
written languages used today, paper work...
lost and lots of paperwork.
MC
Thankfully everyone uses the same spoken
language or trade and stuff between kingdoms
and empires would be a nightmate.
MC
Had to copy the laws here in the Kingdom of
Life. Anyone who's traveled borders knows
that you can be caught off guard with certain
laws.
MC
For example, the Kingdom of Life has a law that
makes it illegal to pluch weeds and just leave
them on the ground. You have to either use
it for compost, or to feed animals.
MC
This book's kind of fading so I'm rewriting it
in my spare time. Have to use charcoal for now
though. I'll make a more permenant copy once
I have more ink I can use.
MC
Ah right, my friend's sister wanted me to
rate her poetry. Was never my thing, so...
MC
A map of the Kingdom of life. Never hurts to
know where you are in the world after all.
MC
A map of the city I'm from... I almost miss
home... almost. I'm happier studying ancient
ruins and reading history books.
MC
Really need to write to mom at some point.
She worries for me more than my father ever
will. I am just an object to him. Wouldn't be
suprised if he gets himself killed.
MC
Sleep potions that I... somethimes use. I know
I need sleep, but when I make a big discovery
with this temple, I can't help but to write down
everything I can.
MC
Always regret it after, so I need to drink
these to fall asleep on those nights.
MC
A very dusty globe I found in the temple. It's
hard to clean since it seems like there's a
thin layer of glue holding the dust to it.
MC
I'll have to look into something that won't
ruin the map on it. From what I can see on the
map though, the lands are completly different
from what the map today looks like.
MC
If it is different from today's map, then this
place is older than anything that can be
recorded, which is exciting!
MC
It means that everything I found here shouldn't
exist and yet it does. If I had to guess, there
is magic or something that has somehow kept
this place in tact.
MC
It makes me wonder if I should bring a mage
here to see if any of them can figure out the
magic from eons past. If they can, it might
solve the magic crisis that we're facing.
MC
Some empty scrolls and envelopes found in one
of the bedrooms for the temple workers. I
assume that they're for writing holy scripture
or inviting people to the temple.
MC
Some jewlery from one of the side rooms near
the main entrance to the temple. It was most
certainly stuff that people brought and took
off before they entered the ceremonies.
MC
Some jewlery from one of the side rooms near
the main entrance to the temple. It was most
certainly stuff that people brought and took
off before they entered the ceremonies.
MC
A crown of all things to be in the side rooms.
The god worshiped here must have been loved a
lot to have a king or queen visit.
MC
Very fancy rings I found under the crown.
Whoever the king or queen was, they loved
expensive stuff.
MC
Almost makes me wonder if one of them is a key
or something with how intricate they are. Not
to mention the very feint magic energy I can
feel when they're in my hand.
MC
These letters and scrolls have some writing on
them, but they don't seem to be complete.
There's a heart on a crumpled letter, so maybe
they're love letters that never sat right?
MC
The one book in this place that has no age it
seems. It was found on the center pedistal
on the central stage. Even just holding this
I can feel a divine power. Weak now, but there.
MC
Letters that are sealed and have some writing
on the outside. I'm scared to open them to see
the writing on the inside since they're already
falling apart, so I'll not touch them further.
MC
I found this in one of the sinks in a kitchen.
Not sure what a necklace is doing in there, but
it's pretty rusty. I think a shop in the air
kingdom has some anti rust something.
MC
Empty jars that had a thin layer of dust.
they weren't that hard to clean with the water
in the temple.
MC
I found these potions in one of the bedrooms
and no longer want to touch them. Tried a small
sip of one of these, and was high as a griffin
for the rest of the day. Strong stuff.
MC
Whoever used these must have had a lot of
stress... or was a junkie, either or.
MC
Found these all with the same symbol on them.
With how fancy the scrolls are, I can only
assume that the head priest used them to write
the most holy text for selling.
MC
Not everyone who would have been able to visit
in the time would have been able to stay, so
these must have been copies of the most
important vows of the faith.
MC
This theory is supported because the writing on
all of them is the exact same, even if I can't
actually read the language.
MC
Spices from one of the kitchens. There's
something to be learned from old spices...
MC
if any of them survived the test of time that
is. They all look rotten on the inside, so it's
best not to open them. This place isn't the
best smelling already, so let's avoid worse.
MC
Three large vaces of liquid. The liquid is all
the same, just different colored glass. As
far as I can tell, the liquid is water.
MC
Drawings of a young looking male in various
poses. The man has a slim figure and long hair.
By the looks of it, their clothes are light
while their hair is darker.
MC
One of them has some color, brow for the hair
and eyes. It looks like the cothing is white
and has green vines around his body as if they
are sprouting from him directly. Odd..
MC
A box full of some intricate looking ceramic
pottery. Cups, plates, bowls, and even a spoon
with fork like prongs at the end. Honestly
should get myself one, this seems useful.
MC
Another box of jewlery, but this one has some
writing on the front of it. If I had to guess,
this might be a donation box so that the tmeple
can sell the gems for materials they need?
MC
Any archeologist or historian worth their stuff
records everything they've discovered durring
a long project. I don't have anything else to
add to the list at the moment however.
MC
Or at least nothing more until I gain access
to the central grass covered room in the center
of the temple. I need to wait for the crowbar
from ________ though.
MC
Hopefully she'll arrive sooner rather than
later. I can't wait to see what's in that room!
MC
An ancient mage's hat that I found in what I
assume is the office. It's lost it's magic
over the years as far as I can tell, but it's
still soft and clean.
MC
Robes that go with the hat next to it. I can't
figure out what part of the world these would
have come from, but it's not the Life kingdom.
There isn't any vine icongraphy on it.
MC
Ah right, moved the current world map over here
to try and figure out the origin of the robes
and hat. I should move it back soon, but later.
MC
A bunch of pendants in the shape of leaves. I
don't need to guess what these are for. They're
the holy symbol of the temple.
MC
Makes me wonder if this temple is the origin of
the Life Kingdom as we know it. After all, the
Life Kingdom uses plants as their symbols, and
have for as long as the history we know.
MC
Maybe the god worshiped here was a goddess of
good harvest of some kind? It would make sense
for a harvest goddess to be linked to plants
after all.
MC
I'll have to hit my old history books to see.
MC
Table cloths or fabric that wasn't used by the
temple before the temple was abandonded.
MC
Just some of the smithing tools I found in the
forge. I don't know why a temple needed a forge,
but I suppose being able to make your own tools
and such is a good idea.
MC
Why would a temple need armor? There's more
down below, so obviously they needed it, but I
can't imagine there was a need for combat...
Right?
MC
Maybe it was more just protecting against
unruly temple visitors? If this place was as
popular as I think it was, then I could see a
rush for people to get in.
MC
Armor and shields would help with that quite a
bit I suppose.
MC
Helmets to go along with the armor. These two
full sets of armor, helmets, shields
were really heavy. Makes me even more curious
as to why these were needed.
MC
This suit of armor was exactly my size, so
getting it out of the temple was easy since
I could just wear it and climb the ropes.
MC
Thank you father for teaching me how to wear
heavy armor, even if I prefer lighter armor
if any with my combat style.
MC
Suprisingly, the armor of this ancient time is
more advanced than armor made today. Not by a
lot, but the amount of detail on this armor
can't be done with today's techonology.
MC
A young child's clothing by the look of it.
Kids being dragged to places they more than
likely don't want to be... some things never
change it seems.
MC
Although I suppose it's possible the god here
was so well loved that even kids wanted to
come here... I know that I wouldn't have wanted
to come here as a kid though, so who knows?
MC
A similar set of clothes to the clothing next
to this, but much more... bulky? If I had to
guess, the ancient dwarves also paid their
respects to this god.
MC
I can't imagine the stubborn dwarves actually
worshiping a god though, so maybe this was a
dwarf who was banished from the clans? That's
the only explanation I can think of.
MC
It's always a pain to collect firewood. Even
worse if it's for making charcoal since I need
so much more of it.
MC
I was worried about water for a while when I
was building the house, so I tried digging for
water and found a pocket of it here. Water is
a must for survival after all.
MC
It's also needed for watering crops so that
I don't starve to death either.
MC
Laundry sucks to do, but even I can't stand
dirty clothing. Although my reasoning is...
not what it should be. I don't care about my
smell, I care about bringing grime inside.
MC
I refuse to dirty the inside of the temple,
since that'd harm history.
MC
Couldn't bring myself to cut down this lonesome
tree. It's provided me so much shade when
building or farming.
MC
Doesn't hurt that the tree supplies me with a
steady supply of apples. I harvested them
yesterday however so it'll be a while before
I can harvest more.
MC
Couldn't bring myself to cut down this lonesome
tree. It's provided me so much shade when
building or farming.
MC
Doesn't hurt that the tree supplies me with a
steady supply of apples. I harvested them
yesterday however so it'll be a while before
I can harvest more.
MC
Harvested all these apples from the tree
outside yesterday. It was more than normal, so
I'm at a loss as to what to make with them. I
don't think I can eat apples all day every day.
MC
Recently had a shipment of carrots come in, so
I'll need to cook something with them. I think
I still have the resources to make carrot cake
around here, so maybe that?
MC
Flour that I have to figure something out with
but it can wait. I'm really close to making
a huge discovery with the temple!
MC
Flour that I have to figure something out with
but it can wait. I'm really close to making
a huge discovery with the temple!
MC
Never hurts to have some wine with your cooking.
Maybe I'll celebrate with ______ once I make
my huge discovery in this place.
MC
I should make some apple jam soon with the
apples I've collected. Need to used these jars
at some point. Could also make some berry jam
now that I think about it.
MC
What little money I have from when I first came
here. I'd estimate that all in all it's probably
worth... 1000G?
MC
Honestly, gold and silver bars aren't worth
that much. I should have grabbed the iron
and steel. Those would have sold for a lot more
whenever I need money for this dig.
MC
I guess if I sell them to a rich fart they'd be
worth a lot, but the vast majority of people in
the world prefer practicality.
MC
Log book of transactions I've made. Always
smart to keep track of that kind of stuff.
Prevents shady people from trying to get money
from you.
MC
A few healing potions I have left over from
when I ordered them after I got a strain trying
to open the big iron gate leading to the last
room of the temple.
MC
Ah right, my friend who delivers my stuff
brought some spices for me to try when I cook.
Need to use these soon. The same food over and
over does get old.
MC
Some soap and perfume I asked for from ______.
I'm running out of money, so I need it to
reenter a more social space. Helps that she
loves her herbs and soap making.
MC
Getting it for free is nice since she usually
charges quite high for it. I recall her telling
me that one order ended up bringing her more
than 50,000G.
MC
Always got to have a bit of dry food storage.
MC
A bit of extra water from the well that I was
storing in case it dried up. I found a spring
of clean water down in the temple before I
needed to use all of this.
MC
I may not need these anymore, but I'd like to
use it up to empty the jars.
MC
A bit of extra water from the well that I was
storing in case it dried up. I found a spring
of clean water down in the temple before I
needed to use all of this.
MC
I may not need these anymore, but I'd like to
use it up to empty the jars.
MC
I'm slowly packing up all of my discoveries
in this temple. There's a museum to the south
that I want to ship all of the important stuff
to.
MC
Some of the less important stuff like chairs
and tables won't be going. Those empty letters
on the main table are another thing that won't
go.
MC
Some contracts I have going to get things I
can't produce myself. Nothing more really to
that.
MC
Contracts for transporting all the stuff I've
found that I'm currently drawing up. I need
to be cautious with how I word these so
nothing gets stolen by the caravans.
MC
I've prepared some basic coin for the transport
that I can use as advance pay. Need to see if
the muesuem will take on the other half of the
payment for transport.
MC
My letters to the mueseum to see if they'll
accept paying for the rest of the transport of
everything here. Can't figure out how I want to
word this however.
MC
At this point, I'm getting tempted to go there
in person and explain things.
MC
There was a lot of dirt and rock that was
filling the tower into the temple. Honestly,
this probably took the most amount of time
now that I'm thinking about it... Worth it!
A
MC
Even more of the dirt I pulled out of the
tower. If I remember right, it took me about a
year just to dig enough dirt out to enter the
temple or church underground.
B
MC
I remember having to take a week off due to
straining my back after one particularly heavy
haul of this dirt. After that, I took my time
since I couldn't work on making my way to
MC
the inside of the temple to study the history
if I couldn't dig.
C

I honestly started wishing I spent half my
money for this dig for an earth orb at about
the half way point. If I had, the job would
have been done so much faster.
MC
That being said though, I probably wouldn't
have had enough money to do the rest of this
dig. It was a hard choice, but staying here
longer was the better choice.
MC
After all, the longer I stay, the more I
discover and learn about the people who lived
and worked here. I would LOVE to unbury the
entire temple, but that would take too long.
D

My collection of world history from the
perspective of the Kingdom of Life. A very
peaceful people. Rarely ever want to fight,
and if they do, it's only in self defense.
MC
My books about the history of the Air Kingdom.
The only kingdom to be split into two halfs.
The first half is the surface, full of people
who are very prideful.
MC
The second half full of overly stubborn
dwarves who live underground. The people on the
surface claim they're air because they live up
here on the surface where there is a lot of it.
MC
The underground dwarves claim it for themselves
due to some tradation that they refuse to share.
It's hard to say who's in the right without the
knowledge of dwarves history.
MC
The estemed Water Nation's history. Why they
live in the desert I have no idea, but to each
their own. Most of their written history is
about the challenges they face in the desert.
MC
The Flaming Empire, a place where fire is
sacred and people can't live without it. I've
heard that it's getting hard for them to live
in the tundra that they live in though.
MC
With elemental magic fading from the world,
they can't keep themselves warm easily anymore.
I just hope they can get good homes when they
leave eventually.
MC
Earth Kingdom history. Almost all of these are
hand written by me back from when I first
started getting into learning as much as I
could about history.
MC
Was brought to their kingdom for trade talks or
something, I forget, but I just read their
history out of boredom, and fell in love with
all of it.
MC
The one good memory of my father was him
letting me copy all of their notes on their
history and later buying me a translation guide
so I could translate once I got home.
MC
Both of these shelves at the end are from the
Death Empire. I was born there, so it makes
sense that I would have more books from there
than anywhere else.
MC
Most of these are written by myself since my
father never cared to see what I was doing with
my day to day life. Was a pain to bring them
all here, but I couldn't live without them.
MC
All the books in this row are survival based.
I needed to survive before I could dig this
place out before anything else after all.
MC
I don't think I need these books anymore
seeing as I memorized them all at this point.
MC
Ah yes, all my childhood books. I didn't need
to bring these with me... probably shouldn't
have, but it's nice to revisit childhood
sometimes.
MC
All the cookbooks I've had over the time I've
lived here. I haven't used them a whole lot,
but it's still nice to have them.
MC
My books with diagrams of various monsters in
the world, and how to survive an encounter
with them.
MC
Granted, most of the advice is to run, unless
you're one of the rare mages of the world. I
remember the count of mages being in the double
digits now compared to even 50 years ago.
MC
Hopefully their research bears fruit soon.

My personal collection of cooking and eating
tools. Didn't have space in the kitchen to
put the full collection there.

A statue depicting a man covered in vines.
